&lt;p&gt;IEEE Communications and Signal Processing Societies Joint Chapter in collaboration with IEEE Vizag Bay Sub Section has organized a &amp;ldquo;One day workshop on Digital Signal Processing using Python through Raspberry Pi&amp;rdquo; hosted at IEEE Student Branch, GITAM (Deemed to be University). &amp;nbsp;The speaker, Dr. G. V. V. Sharma, Associate Professor at the Department of Electrical Engineering, IIT Hyderabad has explained the benefits of using python and raspberry pi in signal processing applications. It is essential for a student to learn the quickest and smartest way to access and utilize the technologies. Instead of going for paid proprietary license software, these open source resources could be used for research and publication purposes. Hands-on laboratory programs emphasizing the real time digital signal processing applications were taught and executed. This workshop helped students in understanding the importance of signal processing in this fast advancing world with new innovations coming through every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Students and Faculty members from various colleges have attended the workshop. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
