&lt;p&gt;The Event was coordinated by Dr. T. S. N Murthy, Vice Chair, CommSoc &amp;amp; SPS joint societies chapter, IEEE Hyderabad Section, Mr. Md. K. M. Chisti, Branch counselor, IEEE Student Branch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Invitees:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chair: Dr. HitendraSarma (IEEE)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr. S. Lakshmi Narayana (IEEE)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Theme of the workshop:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Topic: Hyperspectral Image analysis and applications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Image analysis of multiple band imagery has been playing a pertinent role in the field of geo-informatics and remote sensing to analyze and explore the planet Earth. The hyperspectral image analysis is more precise and having contemporary techniques to interpret and analyze the images taken by the sensor having contiguous bands, that makes a big advantage over multispectral image sensors. The workshop covered all the grounds of remote sensing commence at EMR spectrum, covering various statistical techniques to process the data to the applications of hyperspectral image analysis in Precision agriculture, atmospheric studies and mining. In addition to that there were a multiple hands-on sessions using python language to process the hyperspectral data and obtain more refined images without losing the original information of the input images.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Topics covered on first day&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Introduction to Remote Sensing &amp;ndash; Hyperspectral Imaging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evolution: Multi Spectral to Hyperspectral &amp;ndash; Potential Research Problems &amp;amp; Applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unboxing - Hyperspectral Image Processing &amp;ndash; Tutorial&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lab session-1 on the topics covered on day-1&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Topics covered on second day&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dimensionality Reduction in HIS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advances in Hyperspectral Imaging &amp;ndash; Computing Hardware and Algorithms &amp;ndash; I&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advances in Hyperspectral Imaging &amp;ndash; Computing Hardware and Algorithms &amp;ndash; II&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lab Session -2 on the topics covered on day-2&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Guest Speaker:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr. N. Rama Rao, Speaker (IIST)&lt;/p&gt;

