&lt;p&gt;IEEE Professional Communication Workshop organized by IEEE Vizag Bay Sub Section and Sasi Institute of Technology &amp;amp; Engineering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shri K. V. Sriram, Executive Director of Andhra Electronics, Kakinada and Chair,&lt;br /&gt;IEEE Vizag Sub Section was the chief guest for this workshop. This event was conceived and&lt;br /&gt;supposed by Mr. A. Aravindhan, Global Young Professional Representative, IEEE&lt;br /&gt;Professional Communication Society. This workshop is cosponsored by IEEE YP, IEEE&lt;br /&gt;Professional Communication Society, R10 Young Professionals along with SPAA, this&lt;br /&gt;workshop was successfully conducted at Sasi Institute of Technology &amp;amp; Engineering,&lt;br /&gt;Tadepalligudem by SITE IEEE Student Chapter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chief Guest for this workshop Honorable, Shri K. V. Sriram, Chair, IEEE Vizag Bay&lt;br /&gt;Sub Section, Executive Director, Andhra Electronics, Kakinada, acclaimed all the volunteers&lt;br /&gt;and the participants of this workshop. He advised all the participants that being an engineer&lt;br /&gt;the nature of curiosity, experimentation and teaching model should be inculcated with in the&lt;br /&gt;student. As the technology changes for every five years he suggested the students to develop&lt;br /&gt;a sense of &amp;lsquo;I WANT TO CHANGE&amp;rsquo; and it would help the student to think new and explore&lt;br /&gt;things. He stated that the communication is very important but it is being neglected in India.&lt;br /&gt;He advised the students to develop a healthy communications and importance of networking.&lt;br /&gt;Ms A. Nitisha delivered vote of thanks to end the inaugural session.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Day 1 - Session I&lt;br /&gt;Speaker : Mr. K. Ramneek, Wipro Ltd, Bangalore&lt;br /&gt;Topic : Content Writing&lt;/p&gt;
