&lt;p&gt;We are happy that&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;IEEE Vizag Bay Sub Section&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is organized&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Third Professional Meet&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;at&amp;nbsp;Vishnu College of Engineering (Women), Bhimavaram&amp;nbsp;organization on&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;9th Nov 2019&lt;/strong&gt;. Mr. K.V.Sriram, ED, Andhra Electronics, Chair IEEE Vizag Bay Sub Section will address the meeting and followed by a talk by Dr. Sameer Chakarvathi, EC member, IEEE Vizag Bay Sub Section.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With these Meets, IEEE Vizag Bay section trying to connect with the members and organize various events like conference, workshops, training program, distinguished lecture program (DLPs)/volunteer meet, ...&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;in different geographical areas of the Vizag Bay Sub Section (Srikakulam to Vijayawada).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;Followed by &lt;strong&gt;An Invited Talk&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;on &amp;ldquo;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Modeling and optimization in Engineering using evolutionary computing tools&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rdquo; by&amp;nbsp; Dr. VVSS Chakravarthy, Raghu Institute of Technology, Visakhapatnam&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The third IEEE Professional member meet was organized by IEEE Vizag bay sub-section at Shri Vishnu Engineering College for women in Bhimavaram on 9.11.2019. IEEE Vizag bay sub section Chair, Sri Sriram, Dr. VVSS Chakravarthy, EC member of Vizag Bay sub-section and&lt;br /&gt;Dr. PSR Chowdary, professional member have interacted with professional members and students. There are about 30 professional members from various Engineering colleges under&amp;nbsp;vizag bay sub-section have attended in this event. The chair and EC member have explained about the benefits of IEEE, activities which are carried out by Vizag bay sub section, enhancing the professional members and how to strengthen the student branches of respective institutions etc. Later, the professional members have interacted with the team about the issues and challenges they are facing in improving and strengthening the IEEE activities under vizag sub section, and enhancing the student and professional memberships at respective institutions. Some of the student members have also interacted with the team and taken suggestions in improving IEEE activities at the student branch level. Some faculty members have shown their interest in taking new IEEE memberships on this occasion. After the interactive session is over an invited talk was given&amp;nbsp;on &amp;amp;quot;Modeling and optimization in Engineering using evolutionary computing tools&amp;amp;quot; by&amp;nbsp; Dr. VVSS Chakravarthy, to all students and professional members. Followed by invited talk the event was ended with the closing remarks given by Chair and EC members of Vizag bay sub-section.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The dignataries were welcomed by the Dr. Satish Kumar Gudey IEEE SB Counselor on to the dais.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr. Lakshminarayana garu welcomed the guest and thanked him for readily accepting the invitation to give an invited talk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The speaker was introduced by Dr. Satish Kumar Gudey IEEE SB Counselor to the delegates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sri Raghava Murthy garu presented the audience the various satellites the ISRO has launched.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Their characteristics, applications and range are well presented. Control, Principle and remote sensing are the main highlights of the presentation. He also encouraged the students to take up entrepreneurship rather going for campus Jobs. He revealed failures are stepping stones of Success. He explained the students to do innovative work and meet the challenges to scale up in Life.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The inauguration of the IEEE Student branch was started with the Welcome Speech by Dr.Puli Kishore Kumar Sir, head ECE dept. He addressed the guests and introduced them to the Students. The event started around 10AM followed by Mementos and Saplings presented to the honoured guests. Sri K.V. Sriram, Chair IEEE Vizag Bay Sub-Section handed over the Student Branch Formation letter to the Chair of Student Branch. And Students were excited for the first speaker to come. Registrar Sir delivered the welcome address to the guests again and dignitaries and started talking about our Institute and heritage. He also added the students achievements in&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Research, GATE etc. He also added details regarding the composition of students and Permanent campus, that is being currently in development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Around 11AM, Dr. Lakshminarayana Sadasivuni talked about benefits of IEEE membership&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and the year plan-2020 of Student Branch about:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to Run an IEEE Student Branch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to organize technical talks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Benefits to Students with IEEE Membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Benefits to IEEE Professional Members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organizing IEEE Conferences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After about an hour, he presented on &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;AI &amp;amp; Text mining. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;He gave a brief introduction on how&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Google&amp;rsquo;s Page Rank algorithm and Search results optimization. He also added that his&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;research paper helped Google Chrome browser(2007) by adding user characteristics to the browser and making it intelligent for automatic predictions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the post lunch session around 2PM, Dr Abraham Varughese, Scientist - G NSTL DRDO provided a talk on &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Embedded Systems &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;. Many other students from ECE dept have attended for the session. He talked about the applications of Embedded systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inaugural moments&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Student member namely Saiteja Appala and Nikhila Aparna have recorded the most beloved moments in the event.&lt;/p&gt;

