&lt;p&gt;Dean-Academic Program (PG &amp;amp; Research), Gayatri Vidya Parishad College of Engineering&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Autonomous)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Smart Grid : An Opportunity for a sustainable Tomorrow&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dr. A. B. KoteswaraRao, M. Tech.(NIT-Warangal),Ph.D.(IIT-Delhi)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Principal, Gayatri Vidya Parishad College of Engineering&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Autonomous)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Robots : Design issues&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The dignitaries were welcomed by the Dr. Satish Kumar Gudey IEEE SB Counselor on to the dais. Our chief Guest Dr. Lakshminarayana garu addressed the august gathering. He informed the&amp;nbsp; importance of IEEE Student membership to the student members and faculty. He suggested the students to participate in more number of IEEE events to improve their professional life. He also informed all to participate in the coming section student congress. He applauded the speakers for taking time from their busy schedule to ignite the minds of the students with the latest research topics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He was then felicitated with a memento and a shawl by the Principal Dr A B K Rao garu, our Senior Professor and Life Member IEEE Dr Sastry V Vedula garu accompanied by IEEE Vizag bay subsection Vice-Chair Dr Deepika Rani garu, Professors and the IEEE SB Counselor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first talk at 10:30 AM. It was presented by Dr. C V K Bhanu garu on the topic Smart Grid. He showed few videos to motivate the students towards providing solutions to the societal needs. His lecture lasts for about one and half hour comprising of discussions, lecture and motivation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From 12 Pm to 1 PM the students had an ice breaking session comprising of good questionnaire. The successful students were presented goodies by the student chair G Rajesh and vice chair&amp;nbsp; Ritesh Roy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After Lunch, Our beloved Principal Dr A B K Rao garu presented his technical talk on Robots and their design issues. He showed videos of different types of Robots to the audience. He&amp;nbsp; explained the concepts and highlighted the research areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both the speakers were felicitated with a memento after their talks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We had a robotics laboratory session where our faculty members Divya madam, sanjay darwekar, Ramakrishna and Shanker ganesh have shown the two different types of robots and demonstrated them.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;G Rajesh presented the vote of thanks to the esteemed audience.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IEEE Circuits and Systems society and Electron Devices Society joint Chapters of IEEE Hyderabad Section in collaboration with Department of Electronics &amp;amp; Communication Engineering, Raghu Institute of Technology, organized a &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Three day workshop on Advance IoT with Machine Learning&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; during Dec 12-14, 2019. The recently constituted IEEE Circuits and Systems Society (CASS) Chapter of IEEE student branch at Raghu Institute of Technology hosted the event.&amp;nbsp; Mr.Sai Prasanth Kanumuri, Mr. Srikar Somanchi, Mr. Harsha Vardhan Marrisetty, Ms. N V Monalisha Mohanty, Mr. Sai Ramana Ganesh Vasanthavada, Ms. Amrutha Tamarapalli, Ms.Laxmi Jahnavi Vanam, Ms. Shalini Raghupatruni are the student members of the CASS Chapter have also served as teaching assistants in the workshop for which they received appreciation certificates from IEEE Hyderabad Section. Similarly, Mr. O.Santa Ram, Ms. Manisha, Mr. Kamal, Mr. Shiva Balaji, are other IEEE student branch members who have extended their support as volunteers and made the event happening.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There were about 72 participants from various colleges of Visakhapatnam, Vizianagaram, Srikakulam, Krishna, East Godavari and west Godavari Districts. Prof. Md. Arifuddin Sohel, IEEE CAS/ED Societies joint Chapter Chair delivered lectures on Machine Learning and implementation using Python on Jupyter Notebook. Prof. VVSSS Chakravarthy, Mr. Muniruddin, Mr. Badrinath Chitti and Mr.Adithe Sarma have delivered lectures and conducted hands on practice session using Node MCU and Raspberry Pi. The participants have successfully developed various IoT based projects during the hands on sessions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prof. P.Satish Rama Chowdary, IEEE student counsellor, IEEE SB, Raghu Institute of Technology appreciated the performance of the teaching assistants and the volunteers of the workshop. He also mentioned to the participants that the kits used in the workshop are made available in the laboratory of the Department of ECE, RIT to all the participants of the workshop to carry out projects based on Node MCU and Raspberry Pi. The teaching assistants who were active during the workshop are available to extend their support if required.&lt;/p&gt;

